@Pyrat 2It's an 18, if it was a 19 I would have not been able to work on the car since thats the biggest socket in the kit I got..Harbor Freight carries a kit with 6 of these types of sockets worked great while we did the suspension.http://m.harborfreight.com/6-pc-38-i...set-68016.html

OP,strut top mounting bolts are 18mm and not sure if they are single-use "stretch" bolts or if you can use them - I'd buy new just to be safe.Strut brace mount bolts are external T20 torx 10mm bolts c/w collar and are single use only.
